  "prompt": "What is the academic pressure and workload at Williams College like?",
  "response": "Williams College is known for having a rigorous academic environment with a challenging workload. As a highly selective liberal arts college, it attracts motivated students and offers a demanding academic experience. Students typically report:\n\n1. Intense coursework\n- Small class sizes (average around 15 students)\n- Significant reading and writing assignments\n- High expectations for academic performance\n- Emphasis on critical thinking and in-depth analysis\n\n2. Workload characteristics\n- Substantial weekly reading and homework\n- Regular research papers and presentations\n- Collaborative learning and discussion-based classes\n- Academically competitive but generally collaborative environment\n\n3. Academic support\n- Accessible professors\n- Robust academic advising\n- Study resources and tutoring centers\n- Flexible curriculum with diverse course offerings\n\n4. Stress levels\n- Academically challenging\n- High-achieving student body\n- Some students experience significant academic stress\n- Strong support systems to help manage workload\n\nWhile the academic pressure is considerable, Williams also emphasizes student well-being and provides resources to help students manage stress and maintain a balanced lifestyle.\n\nPlease note that individual experiences can vary, and current students or recent graduates would provide the most up-to-date perspective on the academic environment.",
